<div id="sa0b3" style="color: rgb(0, 51, 204);display: none;">Don't cut off the hand that feeds you. Without LMSs, eXe will have difficulty delivering content, even if it's disguised as radical constructivism. We try to export SCORM compliant content for LMSs to deliver - so best to stay in their good books.</div>
<div id="sa1b3" style="color: rgb(0, 51, 204);display: none;">Not a bad idea, but we are still reluctant to undergo operations from surgeons who spent their postgraduate years deconstructing the meaning of a scalpel.</div>
<div id="sa2b3" style="color: rgb(0, 51, 204);display: none;">This is the best option because then you can't be accused of embedding any paradigmitic point of depature.</div>
